// SOURCE: Source Files/Intergrations/Fusion Intergrations 2/Fusion Forge/Product Info Sheet.txt
// NOTE: Integrated into the Fusion FSN tree for migration traceability.
// CONTENT:
// Product Info Sheet: Fusion ForgeExecutive SummaryFusion Forge is the next-generation build system and package manager designed to unify the fragmented landscape of software compilation. While traditional tools like Cargo, CMake, and Pip focus on single languages, Forge is language-agnostic by design. It serves as the single entry point for developing high-performance hybrid applications targeting the Fusion "Supernova" Runtime, as well as maintaining strict backward compatibility with v1 (Native) and v2 (Nebula).Product IdentityName: Fusion ForgeCLI Command: forgeConfiguration: Fusion.tomlCore Philosophy: "Write in anything, deploy as one."Key CapabilitiesPolyglot Dependency Graph: Resolves dependencies across languages. A Rust crate can depend on a C++ library, which depends on a Python script. Forge handles the linking order.Unified Manifest: Replaces Cargo.toml, package.json, requirements.txt, and CMakeLists.txt with a single Fusion.toml.Auto-Bindings: Automatically generates FFI glue code (via Bindgen/PyO3/Wasm-bindgen) when languages interact.Containerization: Builds directly to Fusion Runtime Images (.fri) optimized for Supernova v3.0.Multi-Generation Targeting: seamlessly builds artifacts for:v1 (Legacy): Pure native binaries (Rust/C++ + GPU/QPU).v2.0 (Nebula Core): Strict sandboxed WASM plugins (No host access).v2.1 (Nebula Enhanced): Bidirectional WASM (Host calls, GPU/QPU requests).v3 (Supernova): Full hybrid distributed mesh.Supported Toolchains (v1.0)Fusion Lang: Native support.Rust: Wraps cargo with enhanced caching.C++: Wraps clang/cmake with auto-module mapping.Python: Integrates uv for blazing fast package resolution (v3+ only).JavaScript/TypeScript: Integrates bun for bundling (v2+ only).Target AudienceSystem Architects: Building hybrid clouds (e.g., Rust control plane + C++ data plane).AI Engineers: integrating Python models into low-latency C++ or Rust pipelines.Full Stack Devs: Managing backend (Rust) and frontend (TS) in a monorepo.Migration Teams: Moving legacy v1/Nebula workloads to the Supernova mesh.
